British American Tobacco’s Zimbabwe Unit Says it Records Fiscal Year Loss

-- B y   N e l s o n   G o r e   B a n y a
-- 
2011-04-12T08:39:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/british-american-tobacco-s-zimbabwe-unit-says-it-records-fiscal-year-loss.html
British American Tobacco Plc (BATS) ’s
Zimbabwean unit posted a loss of $499,000 for 2010, compared to
a profit of $300,000 a year earlier, according to a statement
published in the Herald newspaper.  The company cited higher expenses driven by an increase in
the price of leaf tobacco, the Harare-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nelson Gore Banya in Johannesburg at 
 ngbanya@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Agnes Nikoi at 
 anikoi@bloomberg.net  